Fastdev is a Swedish software development company founded in 2007 with the goal of delivering world-class software development services to its clients. Today we are a team of around 100 specialists based in Stockholm or remote around the globe and we keep growing rapidly. The customers we work with are mainly Scandinavian companies operating in a variety of fields like financial, insurance, gaming, well-being, tourism, automotive, e-commerce and more. The technological scope we work with is just as diverse and covers front end/back end development, machine learning, IoT, cloud services and others.










 Some of our values are:









* We strive for excellence. We're damn good and we aim at doing our very best in every part of our work;
* We put clients’ interests first It goes without saying, but we say it to underline it;
* Clients’ interests first, zeroing on creating the best possible value for them;
* We keep our word. Vital. Both internally and externally- in all cases;
* We believe in our people. Without great people we simply can’t work. We believe that each individual can reach their full potential in the right environment and with the right support;
* We believe in meritocracy. At Fastdev, results merit advancement- simple as that;
* We keep it simple. We acknowledge the cost of complexity in code, functionality and processes and strive for simplicity;
* We are cost-effective.









 We are currently seeking a sales person who thrives in a fast-paced environment where adaptability and creativity are highly valued. As our sales person, you will have individual responsibility and significant freedom to build and develop business relationships with B2B clients. Our success depends on delivering a high-quality offering to our clients, so your ability to communicate our value to new prospects will be crucial.










 You would be a great match if you:









* Have relevant work experience, preferably in service or sales in a software development company;
* Possess endurance, focus on successes, and learn from setbacks;
* Have the ability to juggle multiple tasks at once and are solution-oriented;
* Are stimulated by interacting with other people and by learning about different industries and roles;
* Are curious, proactive, and comfortable with appointment setting over the phone;
* Speak and write fluently in English and Swedish.









 What is in there for you:









* A competitive remuneration, determined according to experience and achievements;
* A full-time regular employment opportunity;
* An attractive performance based commission, based on your successful results;
* A strong internal culture characterized by openness, camaraderie, and a clear value of everyone's well-being and work-life balance.
* A stimulating and varied job with ample development opportunities.
* A wonderful and energized team where we support each other in achieving our goals.
